# Security headers for Cloudflare Pages (and any host that reads _headers).
# Mirror of the vercel.json `headers` block — keep the two in sync.
# Vercel ignores this file (it uses vercel.json); Cloudflare Pages uses it.
# Add the Content-Security-Policy here too once the runtime Tailwind CDN is
# removed (see docs/PRIVACY_SECURITY.md).
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), browsing-topics=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000
